1. First, create a custom control in your shared project (PCL/.NET Standard project).

Create a new class named 'CustomRadioButton' and inherit from 'RadioButton'.

```csharp
using Xamarin.Forms;

namespace CustomRadioButtonApp.Controls
{
    public class CustomRadioButton : RadioButton
    {
        public CustomRadioButton() : base()
        {
        }
    }
}
```

2. Next, create custom renderers for Android and iOS.

**For Android:**

Create a new custom renderer class named 'CustomRadioButtonRenderer' in the Android project. Inherit from 'RadioButtonRenderer' and add the ExportRenderer attribute.

```csharp
using CustomRadioButtonApp.Controls;
using Xamarin.Forms.Platform.Android;

[assembly: Xamarin.Forms.ExportRenderer(typeof(CustomRadioButton), typeof(CustomRadioButtonApp.Droid.Renderers.CustomRadioButtonRenderer))]
namespace CustomRadioButtonApp.Droid.Renderers
{
    public class CustomRadioButtonRenderer : RadioButtonRenderer
    {
        protected override void OnElementChanged(ElementChangedEventArgs<RadioButton> e)
        {
            base.OnElementChanged(e);
            if (Control != null)
            {
                UpdateButtonColors();
            }
        }

        private void UpdateButtonColors()
        {
            Control.ButtonTintList = Android.Content.Res.ColorStateList.ValueOf(Element.TextColor.ToAndroid());
            Control.SetTextColor(Element.TextColor.ToAndroid());
        }
    }
}
```

**For iOS:**

Create a new custom renderer class named 'CustomRadioButtonRenderer' in the iOS project. Inherit from 'RadioButtonRenderer' and add the ExportRenderer attribute.

```csharp
