To extract a specific certificate from a certificate bundle in bash, you can use tools like `awk` and `grep`. Here's a script that extracts a certificate whose issuer matches a given string:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

# Replace the searchString with the desired issuer string
searchString="Issuer String"

# Replace the bundleFilePath with the path to your cert bundle file
bundleFilePath="path/to/your/cert-bundle.crt"

awk -v search="$searchString" '
  BEGIN { cert = 0; output_block = 0; }

  /-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----/ {
    block = 1;
    buffer = $0RS;
    next;
  }

  /-----END CERTIFICATE-----/ { block = 0; buffer = buffer $0; }

  block { buffer = buffer $0RS; next; }

  /Issuer:/ {
    if (match($0, search)) {
      output_block = 1;
    }
  }

  /^$/ {
    if (output_block) {
      printf "%s", buffer;
      output_block = 0;
    }
  }
' "$bundleFilePath"
```

